= Sugar Cookies

#columns(2)[
  == Equipment

  - Oven
  - Baking tray
  - Bowl; or
  - Electric stand mixer (optional)

  == Ingredients

  - 365g (2 3/4 cup) all-purpose flour
  - 6g (1 tsp.) baking soda
  // TODO: Does this need to be baking powder? Can we try 1/4 tsp. baking soda and 1/2 tsp.
  // white vinegar instead? How about lemon juice instead, for flavor?
  - 2g (1/2 tsp.) baking powder
  - 225g (1 cup) butter, softened
  - 315g (1 1/2) cups white sugar
  - 60g (1 large) egg
  - 5g (1 tsp.) vanilla extract

  #colbreak()

  == Steps

  + Preheat oven to 190°C (375°F).
  + Mix ingredients together in this order:
    + Sugar & butter.
    + Egg & vanilla.
    + Flour, baking soda, & baking powder.
  + Roll dough into small balls on baking sheet.
  + Bake 8-10 minutes. Let cool completely before serving.

  == References

  #set cite(form: "full")

  @ar_sugar-cookies
]
